WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.987 --> 00:00:12.851
The morning God Flame has finally risen
to give us a bit of warmth. Princess.

2
00:00:13.367 --> 00:00:15.046
(DOOR OPENS)

3
00:00:16.037 --> 00:00:18.216
(BELLS JINGLING)

4
00:00:19.123 --> 00:00:21.456
HARMONY: Good morning.
Your Majesty.

5
00:00:22.418 --> 00:00:24.479
QUEEN KANE: It is a beautiful day. Maghra.

6
00:00:24.503 --> 00:00:27.141
The entire city will rejoice with you.

7
00:00:27.340 --> 00:00:32.140
It is a shame Father couldn't be here
with us to celebrate your wedding day.

8
00:00:35.931 --> 00:00:37.276
(SIGHS)

9
00:00:38.100 --> 00:00:41.072
Lilac. lavender and honey.

10
00:00:41.771 --> 00:00:45.291
- (MAGHRA SIGHS)
- You'll make the most appealing bride.

11
00:00:45.650 --> 00:00:46.995
Leave that.

12
00:00:47.360 --> 00:00:50.255
Princess. you must be completely
unadorned for the marriage ceremony.

13
00:00:50.279 --> 00:00:53.383
- No. I will not remove this cuff.
- It's the law of the land.

14
00:00:53.407 --> 00:00:56.129
Handmaiden. what is your name?

15
00:00:57.078 --> 00:00:58.680
Harmony. Your Majesty.

16
00:00:58.704 --> 00:01:01.759
Harmony? That is a beautiful name.

17
00:01:02.875 --> 00:01:04.310
Give me your hand. Harmony.

18
00:01:04.334 --> 00:01:06.931
(BELLS JINGLING)

19
00:01:10.257 --> 00:01:12.103
Harmony.

20
00:01:12.426 --> 00:01:15.989
are you in the habit of telling princesses
what they may and may not do?

21
00:01:16.013 --> 00:01:19.076
Perhaps you would tell your queen as well?

22
00:01:19.100 --> 00:01:21.078
(GASPS)
No. Your Majesty. never.

23
00:01:21.102 --> 00:01:23.114
Then hush and leave her.

24
00:01:28.025 --> 00:01:32.381
Hmm. The princess is fully slathered.
You may go. Harmony.

25
00:01:32.405 --> 00:01:33.845
Yes. Your Majesty.

26
00:01:36.325 --> 00:01:37.712
(SIGHS)

27
00:01:42.707 --> 00:01:43.892
(DOOR CLOSES)

28
00:01:43.916 --> 00:01:47.562
The Pennsan people.
and that means all of them.

29
00:01:47.586 --> 00:01:52.693
even insignificant servants.
must believe this is a true union.

30
00:01:52.717 --> 00:01:55.112
Don't worry.
I will play my part.

31
00:01:55.136 --> 00:01:56.905
You're not in this alone.

32
00:01:56.929 --> 00:02:00.902
Yes. I am.
You are not the one being unfaithful.

33
00:02:02.351 --> 00:02:03.738
(SIGHS)

34
00:02:04.603 --> 00:02:07.617
This marriage will serve us all.

35
00:02:07.856 --> 00:02:10.836
When your children are found
and brought here to you.

36
00:02:10.860 --> 00:02:13.932
it'll be this arrangement
that'll keep them safe.

37
00:02:14.280 --> 00:02:18.002
(TUNING FORK ECHOES)

38
00:02:18.868 --> 00:02:22.097
Some people would be insulted
by their sister tuning them out.

39
00:02:22.121 --> 00:02:24.599
Sibeth. you can never be silenced.

40
00:02:24.623 --> 00:02:26.511
God knows I've tried.

41
00:02:34.759 --> 00:02:36.104
Here.

42
00:02:38.304 --> 00:02:43.027
Remember when you were little.
and I'd wash your hair?

43
00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:51.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

44
00:03:05.206 --> 00:03:06.801
Don't stop.

45
00:03:10.878 --> 00:03:12.223
Please.

46
00:05:07.662 --> 00:05:10.807
Can you please just...
just stay back?

47
00:05:10.831 --> 00:05:13.518
I promise you. no one is going
to kill me on this path.

48
00:05:13.542 --> 00:05:15.729
Yeah. well. not with me here.
they're not.

49
00:05:15.753 --> 00:05:18.899
Haniwa.
Haniwa. wait for me.

50
00:05:18.923 --> 00:05:21.568
(GRUNTS. SIGHS)

51
00:05:21.592 --> 00:05:27.616
Listen. there's no harm in having
a... a dedicated warrior by your side.

52
00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:30.507
I know I'm grateful
for you and your arrows.

53
00:05:32.645 --> 00:05:34.449
I can hear you thinking.

54
00:05:35.064 --> 00:05:36.492
(SCOFFS)

55
00:05:38.275 --> 00:05:41.372
Yesterday. I was mourning my mother.

56
00:05:41.946 --> 00:05:44.334
Today. she is a living princess.

57
00:05:44.657 --> 00:05:48.671
and I am thinking back
on every moment of my childhood.

58
00:05:49.120 --> 00:05:52.258
wondering what was true and what still is.

59
00:05:54.250 --> 00:05:56.346
We will know soon. my love.

60
00:05:57.044 --> 00:05:58.765
Not soon enough.

61
00:06:00.381 --> 00:06:01.893
(PARIS GROANS)

62
00:06:02.341 --> 00:06:03.770
(SIGHS. EXCLAIMS)

63
00:06:04.468 --> 00:06:07.732
You know. uh.
I'm not a threat to you.

64
00:06:10.016 --> 00:06:12.862
You mistake my contempt for fear.

65
00:06:15.479 --> 00:06:20.620
Tell me. Witchfinder General.
how many lives have you taken?

66
00:06:21.527 --> 00:06:25.124
Enough to damn my soul many times over.

67
00:06:26.699 --> 00:06:30.338
And yet. you will kill the queen
whom you have served.

68
00:06:31.537 --> 00:06:34.175
There is not enough damnation for you.

69
00:06:34.957 --> 00:06:38.346
No. I suspect not.

70
00:06:39.503 --> 00:06:42.141
(PANTING)

71
00:06:45.009 --> 00:06:46.236
Mmm.

72
00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:49.440
- Are you all right?
- Yeah. I'm fine.

73
00:06:50.264 --> 00:06:54.278
- We should've stayed another night.
- Nah. it's nothing.

74
00:06:55.019 --> 00:06:58.999
If your head fell off. you would
pick it up and carry it to Pennsa.

75
00:06:59.023 --> 00:07:01.209
No. I would make you carry it.

76
00:07:01.233 --> 00:07:03.754
- (CHUCKLES)
- (CHUCKLES) Ouch.

77
00:07:03.778 --> 00:07:06.089
(BANGING)

78
00:07:06.113 --> 00:07:07.924
These brave soldiers died

79
00:07:07.948 --> 00:07:12.880
trying to stop the murderer. Baba Voss.
from escaping Trivantes.

80
00:07:13.204 --> 00:07:16.224
They died heroes.
and they will be avenged.

81
00:07:16.248 --> 00:07:17.643
(SOBBING)

82
00:07:17.667 --> 00:07:20.995
A valiant soldier
of the republic remembered forever.

83
00:07:21.587 --> 00:07:25.560
A sacred son of Trivantes.
now one with us.

84
00:07:26.008 --> 00:07:28.104
(WOMAN CRYING)

85
00:07:33.641 --> 00:07:36.487
WOMAN: Rendayo.
My son.

86
00:07:42.692 --> 00:07:44.162
Madame Orrie.

87
00:07:45.569 --> 00:07:48.006
Rendayo was a patriot and a hero.

88
00:07:48.030 --> 00:07:49.383
(SNIFFLING)

89
00:07:49.407 --> 00:07:53.629
I immensely admired him
as if he were my own son.

90
00:07:55.788 --> 00:08:00.386
Those responsible for his death
will suffer. You have my word.

91
00:08:01.043 --> 00:08:04.891
(WOMAN CRIES)

92
00:08:11.929 --> 00:08:13.274
(SNIFFLES)

93
00:08:15.850 --> 00:08:21.616
(CRYING)

94
00:08:33.451 --> 00:08:35.053
You have news for me?

95
00:08:35.077 --> 00:08:38.932
Yes. General Voss.
A Witchfinder looking for asylum.

96
00:08:38.956 --> 00:08:40.183
A Witchfinder.

97
00:08:40.207 --> 00:08:42.101
If true. this will be the first time

98
00:08:42.125 --> 00:08:45.069
one of Tamacti Jun's soldiers
has broken ranks.

99
00:08:46.547 --> 00:08:47.816
What is he trading?

100
00:08:47.840 --> 00:08:50.736
He insists he will speak only to you.

101
00:08:50.760 --> 00:08:52.105
Ah.

102
00:08:52.428 --> 00:08:54.774
And he will likely regret that.

103
00:08:54.930 --> 00:08:56.275
Bring him to me.

104
00:08:57.099 --> 00:09:00.446
- GUARD: Come on.
- (GRUNTING. GROANING)

105
00:09:06.776 --> 00:09:12.257
I am Commander General Edo Voss.
and I understand you wish to speak to me.

106
00:09:12.281 --> 00:09:13.342
Yes. sir.

107
00:09:13.366 --> 00:09:16.261
You are the first
of the queen's Witchfinders that I've met

108
00:09:16.285 --> 00:09:20.466
that wasn't already impaled
on the end of my sword.

109
00:09:20.748 --> 00:09:23.281
I have information you will want. sir.

110
00:09:24.210 --> 00:09:29.441
And why would I trust a soldier
who betrays his own kingdom?

111
00:09:29.465 --> 00:09:32.937
My kingdom is no longer
the kingdom I swore to defend.

112
00:09:33.094 --> 00:09:34.564
And how's that?

113
00:09:34.804 --> 00:09:36.698
I am sworn to protect the Payan kingdom

114
00:09:36.722 --> 00:09:38.867
from the evils of witchcraft
and therefore...

115
00:09:38.891 --> 00:09:42.245
I am familiar with Witchfinders. boy.

116
00:09:42.269 --> 00:09:46.166
Including those who might have sight
or seek to facilitate its return.

117
00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:49.127
EDO VOSS: And now.
your queen decrees that the sighted

118
00:09:49.151 --> 00:09:51.331
are. in fact.
not witches.

119
00:09:52.738 --> 00:09:54.675
(STAMMERS)
Yes. sir.

120
00:09:54.699 --> 00:10:00.298
In fact. she also claims to be
carrying a sighted child in her own womb.

121
00:10:01.080 --> 00:10:02.140
Yes. sir.

122
00:10:02.164 --> 00:10:08.522
Boy. did you really desert your own army
and face certain death

123
00:10:08.546 --> 00:10:13.436
to come here and tell me something
my spies reported days ago?

124
00:10:15.428 --> 00:10:18.907
- Hobble him and sell him to the Slavers.
- DAX: No. no.

125
00:10:18.931 --> 00:10:20.611
- GUARD: Come on.
- Sir.

126
00:10:21.058 --> 00:10:24.386
- Commander Voss. there are others.
- EDO VOSS: Stop!

127
00:10:34.947 --> 00:10:36.292
Others?

128
00:10:36.991 --> 00:10:41.279
Hers won't be the first sighted child
within the Payan royal family.

129
00:10:41.329 --> 00:10:43.675
There are two.
already grown.

130
00:10:47.460 --> 00:10:49.764
And these children already grown…

131
00:10:51.422 --> 00:10:55.895
Is one of them a girl called Haniwa?

132
00:10:57.094 --> 00:10:58.439
DAX: Yes.

133
00:11:00.556 --> 00:11:01.901
EDO VOSS: Mmm.

134
00:11:31.837 --> 00:11:33.558
So. this is Pennsa?

135
00:11:35.966 --> 00:11:37.311
Yes.

136
00:11:46.352 --> 00:11:48.032
Is it always this quiet?

137
00:11:49.689 --> 00:11:53.202
(SIGHS)
No. Never.

138
00:11:56.362 --> 00:11:57.802
Something's wrong.

139
00:12:07.498 --> 00:12:09.302
There's soldiers ahead.

140
00:12:12.545 --> 00:12:14.640
Stay here and say nothing.

141
00:12:15.297 --> 00:12:18.603
- Uh. should we be worried?
- Not we. you.

142
00:12:39.447 --> 00:12:41.959
- (HORSE NICKERS)
- (TOAD SIGHS)

143
00:12:42.867 --> 00:12:45.679
- This is gonna be tricky.
- Why? Isn't my mother here?

144
00:12:45.703 --> 00:12:48.466
- She's here.
- So. what's the problem?

145
00:12:49.123 --> 00:12:51.101
The thing of it is…
(SIGHS)

146
00:12:51.125 --> 00:12:53.792
…she's apparently getting married today.

147
00:13:09.977 --> 00:13:11.489
Baba. my love…

148
00:13:13.064 --> 00:13:14.450
Forgive me.

149
00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:17.495
KOFUN: Mom?

150
00:13:19.570 --> 00:13:20.914
Mom!

151
00:13:21.238 --> 00:13:22.583
Kofun?

152
00:13:23.199 --> 00:13:27.296
- Mom. Mom! Mom! (CHUCKLES)
- (GASPS)

153
00:13:28.454 --> 00:13:32.601
Whew. (GASPS)
You're alive.

154
00:13:32.625 --> 00:13:34.220
My baby.

155
00:13:35.586 --> 00:13:40.560
Oh. I've searched for you
every day since we were separated.

156
00:13:41.092 --> 00:13:42.736
I never stopped.

157
00:13:42.760 --> 00:13:47.574
Mmm. Mom they said
that you're getting married today.

158
00:13:47.598 --> 00:13:49.998
That can't be true. can it?
(INHALES)

159
00:13:50.226 --> 00:13:52.030
I will explain everything.

160
00:13:53.729 --> 00:13:56.367
Where's your father?
And Haniwa?

161
00:13:57.358 --> 00:13:59.586
He went into Trivantes to get her back.

162
00:13:59.610 --> 00:14:00.671
Trivantes?

163
00:14:00.695 --> 00:14:02.839
- (KNOCKING)
- HARMONY: Princess Maghra. it's time.

164
00:14:02.863 --> 00:14:06.468
Wait. Why... Why Trivantes?

165
00:14:06.492 --> 00:14:09.137
- What happened with Jerlamarel?
- How can you be getting married today?

166
00:14:09.161 --> 00:14:11.223
HARMONY: Lord Harlan is waiting.
and the queen is growing impatient.

167
00:14:11.247 --> 00:14:13.514
- I'm coming.
- Who is Lord Harlan?

168
00:14:13.624 --> 00:14:15.602
I will explain everything later.
I have to go. Kofun.

169
00:14:15.626 --> 00:14:19.231
- I just need you to trust me.
- Mama? (WHISPERS) Mama. you can't do this.

170
00:14:19.255 --> 00:14:22.101
I... I can't stop this.

171
00:14:22.383 --> 00:14:23.443
Your father would understand.

172
00:14:23.467 --> 00:14:26.863
No. I don't think he would understand why
his dead wife is marrying someone else.

173
00:14:26.887 --> 00:14:28.281
- Kofun...
- Stop saying my name

174
00:14:28.305 --> 00:14:29.866
and do something to fix this!

175
00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:33.245
I... I don't know what is happening.
Mama. but you can't go through with it.

176
00:14:33.269 --> 00:14:34.781
Be quiet!

177
00:14:35.271 --> 00:14:39.619
I am still the mother you knew.
and you are still my son.

178
00:14:40.234 --> 00:14:42.372
But things have changed.

179
00:14:43.571 --> 00:14:46.959
Now. I'm doing this for you
and for all of us.

180
00:14:47.825 --> 00:14:51.297
So you stay here.
You stay here in my room.

181
00:14:51.620 --> 00:14:53.424
and you speak to no one.

182
00:14:54.332 --> 00:14:58.262
and then we will talk
when all of this is over. I promise.

183
00:15:00.171 --> 00:15:03.434
- I promise.
- (GRUNTS) D-Don't do this.

184
00:15:04.967 --> 00:15:06.834
- Don't do this.
- I have to.

185
00:15:17.021 --> 00:15:20.451
I have so many questions.

186
00:15:21.067 --> 00:15:25.123
(BABA VOSS RETCHES. SNIFFS. GROANS)

187
00:15:25.696 --> 00:15:28.835
(COUGHING)

188
00:15:29.075 --> 00:15:30.761
- (COUGHS)
- All right. that's enough.

189
00:15:30.785 --> 00:15:33.263
- Ah. I just need a moment. (SIGHS)
- Paris?

190
00:15:33.287 --> 00:15:35.015
- (BABA VOSS GRUNTS)
- (PANTING)

191
00:15:35.039 --> 00:15:38.177
(BABA VOSS GRUNTS. SIGHS)

192
00:15:38.626 --> 00:15:40.562
- (GRUNTS) Woman.
- Oh!

193
00:15:40.586 --> 00:15:43.349
I feel the fever through your clothing.

194
00:15:43.839 --> 00:15:47.020
- It's not gonna kill me.
- You need a healer.

195
00:15:47.176 --> 00:15:48.654
We'll find one in Pennsa.

196
00:15:48.678 --> 00:15:51.649
Baba.
You'll be dead by the time we get there.

197
00:15:53.015 --> 00:15:55.994
We are in the Lakelands now.
not far from the Valier.

198
00:15:56.018 --> 00:15:58.698
They will offer us shelter and a healer.

199
00:15:59.230 --> 00:16:00.575
Papa?

200
00:16:01.524 --> 00:16:04.662
- (SIGHS)
- Please.

201
00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:07.957
Okay. my love.

202
00:16:08.489 --> 00:16:12.009
TAMACTI JUN: I cannot accompany you
to Valier territory.

203
00:16:12.034 --> 00:16:13.971
Well. that is where we are going.

204
00:16:13.995 --> 00:16:17.300
Understand. the hidden tribes
were not hidden to me.

205
00:16:17.832 --> 00:16:20.845
The Valier suffered greatly at my hands.

206
00:16:29.176 --> 00:16:33.858
You stay quiet and camp nearby.
We'll find you on the way out.

207
00:16:34.932 --> 00:16:36.861
(SIGHS. SNIFFLES)

208
00:16:37.935 --> 00:16:39.364
Or not.

209
00:16:40.980 --> 00:16:42.325
(SPITS)

210
00:16:42.481 --> 00:16:43.993
(BABA VOSS GROANS)

211
00:17:06.795 --> 00:17:13.062
(QUEEN KANE. CROWD VOCALIZING)

212
00:17:27.318 --> 00:17:31.040
Our God.
beyond your flame above…

213
00:17:32.782 --> 00:17:35.469
let your will be done on this special day

214
00:17:35.493 --> 00:17:38.214
in this holiest of unions.

215
00:17:39.872 --> 00:17:43.393
Give guidance. clear paths.

216
00:17:43.417 --> 00:17:50.059
condemn those who trespass against us
to writhe within your fire and smoke.

217
00:17:50.966 --> 00:17:57.483
For Thine is the darkness.
the power and the glory.

218
00:17:58.766 --> 00:18:01.029
Forever and ever.

219
00:18:23.541 --> 00:18:28.181
Princess Maghra and Lord Harlan…

220
00:18:32.466 --> 00:18:35.980
You enter this union
adorned in scented splendor.

221
00:18:43.019 --> 00:18:44.947
(CLICKS TONGUE)

222
00:18:48.733 --> 00:18:50.495
(CLICKS TONGUE)

223
00:18:55.781 --> 00:18:58.677
You've pledged
your commitment to each other

224
00:18:58.701 --> 00:19:02.173
with the joining of bodies and souls
before God.

225
00:19:03.539 --> 00:19:10.848
So. by the divine ordination
bestowed upon me. you may seal your union.

226
00:19:18.137 --> 00:19:23.111
(CHEERING)

227
00:19:39.992 --> 00:19:42.171
(BELLS JINGLING)

228
00:20:44.056 --> 00:20:46.589
- (WOMAN MURMURS)
- Thank you. you too.

229
00:20:46.851 --> 00:20:48.531
- (MAN SHOUTS)
- (GASPS)

230
00:20:49.311 --> 00:20:50.990
(SIGHS)

231
00:20:51.230 --> 00:20:53.534
Princess Maghra.

232
00:20:54.942 --> 00:20:59.999
- Any wife of Harlan's is a sister of mine.
- Maghra. you remember my brother.

233
00:21:00.364 --> 00:21:05.088
- HARLAN: Thank you.
- Kerrigan. I changed your diapers.

234
00:21:05.328 --> 00:21:08.223
Well. Lucky for all of us.
I have people for that now.

235
00:21:08.247 --> 00:21:10.767
(CHUCKLES. SNIFFS. GRUNTS)

236
00:21:10.791 --> 00:21:12.519
(CHUCKLES)

237
00:21:12.543 --> 00:21:14.876
- Thank you.
- (MAGHRA CHUCKLES) Oh.

238
00:21:15.379 --> 00:21:17.607
- HARLAN: Thank you so much.
- Oh.

239
00:21:17.631 --> 00:21:19.977
- I'm sorry. Sorry.
- KERRIGAN: Mmm.

240
00:21:20.676 --> 00:21:23.189
All right. Go. go.
Get off. Go.

241
00:21:36.651 --> 00:21:39.087
- CHARLOTTE: Are we close?
- PARIS: Yes.

242
00:21:39.111 --> 00:21:41.381
Because I don't think
the big one can make it much further.

243
00:21:41.405 --> 00:21:43.091
and I don't think
we'll be able to carry him.

244
00:21:43.115 --> 00:21:44.627
(SHUSHES)

245
00:21:46.452 --> 00:21:48.263
- Who's there?
- (METAL SCRAPING)

246
00:21:48.287 --> 00:21:49.389
Make yourself known.

247
00:21:49.413 --> 00:21:53.226
MAN: Who enters Valier territory
without announcing themselves?

248
00:21:53.250 --> 00:21:57.522
Brother! We bring no threat.
I am Paris.

249
00:21:57.546 --> 00:21:59.566
We are the last of the Alkenny.

250
00:21:59.590 --> 00:22:03.229
No. I am last of the Alkenny.

251
00:22:04.220 --> 00:22:06.657
- Chet-chet.
- Chet-chet-chet.

252
00:22:06.681 --> 00:22:08.776
Bow!
(CHUCKLING. EXCLAIMING)

253
00:22:08.933 --> 00:22:10.077
Lion.

254
00:22:10.101 --> 00:22:15.207
- PARIS: Ah. Bow Lion. (CHUCKLES)
- (CHUCKLES)

255
00:22:15.231 --> 00:22:16.868
(SNIFFS)
Oh. Paris.

256
00:22:44.218 --> 00:22:45.658
QUEEN KANE: Kofun?

257
00:22:46.804 --> 00:22:48.804
- Is it you?
- (SWORD CLATTERS)

258
00:22:50.182 --> 00:22:51.862
It's okay.
You're safe.

259
00:22:52.476 --> 00:22:54.156
I'm your Aunt Sibeth.

260
00:22:56.814 --> 00:23:00.294
I was overjoyed
when I heard you were finally here.

261
00:23:00.318 --> 00:23:03.373
We've been waiting
such a long time for you.

262
00:23:04.196 --> 00:23:07.293
(BELLS JINGLING)

263
00:23:12.371 --> 00:23:13.971
Will you embrace me?

264
00:23:24.550 --> 00:23:27.897
(GASPING)

265
00:23:29.096 --> 00:23:30.525
(GASPS)

266
00:23:36.479 --> 00:23:38.612
You're taller than your parents.

267
00:23:41.233 --> 00:23:44.796
Would you like something?
Anything to drink? I'll send for it.

268
00:23:44.820 --> 00:23:47.709
No. Thank you.

269
00:23:48.908 --> 00:23:52.463
How tragic we're only meeting now
for the first time.

270
00:23:54.288 --> 00:23:56.467
You hunted us my whole life.

271
00:24:00.211 --> 00:24:02.648
If only Maghra
had announced herself long ago.

272
00:24:02.672 --> 00:24:06.185
I would've protected her.
protected you.

273
00:24:06.926 --> 00:24:08.479
She knew that.

274
00:24:09.345 --> 00:24:12.449
We were hunting Jerlamarel
and his children.

275
00:24:12.473 --> 00:24:14.673
I didn't know they were Maghra's.

276
00:24:14.850 --> 00:24:18.664
I'd been led to believe
Jerlamarel had killed my sister.

277
00:24:18.688 --> 00:24:20.040
I believed him to be the devil.

278
00:24:20.064 --> 00:24:23.578
You know that's not true.
Why'd my mother stay hidden?

279
00:24:24.735 --> 00:24:26.622
Whatever mistakes she made.

280
00:24:27.405 --> 00:24:31.169
I'm sure she made them
to keep you and your sister safe.

281
00:24:31.450 --> 00:24:33.178
which is what I'm trying to do right now.

282
00:24:33.202 --> 00:24:35.722
Well. even with your decree.

283
00:24:35.746 --> 00:24:38.308
people in Paya still believe
a witch is to be burned.

284
00:24:38.332 --> 00:24:40.865
I've been known to change a few minds.

285
00:24:41.460 --> 00:24:43.397
It might take a bit of time.

286
00:24:43.421 --> 00:24:49.103
but the Payans will learn.
as I have.

287
00:24:50.553 --> 00:24:54.275
to embrace those with sight as blessed.

288
00:24:59.437 --> 00:25:01.366
How difficult for you.

289
00:25:02.523 --> 00:25:06.579
journeying to this place.
arriving on your mother's wedding day.

290
00:25:06.861 --> 00:25:08.994
The world must seem upside down.

291
00:25:10.656 --> 00:25:12.543
But know this.

292
00:25:12.992 --> 00:25:17.507
no one shall stand against you.
not while you're in my kingdom.

293
00:25:18.414 --> 00:25:20.301
Do you believe me?

294
00:25:24.086 --> 00:25:25.431
I don't know.

295
00:25:26.630 --> 00:25:28.017
I want to.

296
00:25:29.633 --> 00:25:31.104
Fair enough.

297
00:25:31.927 --> 00:25:35.733
Many good things start with… desire.

298
00:25:36.223 --> 00:25:38.695
(INHALES)

299
00:25:40.019 --> 00:25:42.532
- (CHUCKLES)
- (BREATHES HEAVILY)

300
00:25:43.773 --> 00:25:47.328
I've arranged a room for you.
We'll talk again soon?

301
00:26:05.086 --> 00:26:08.231
EDO VOSS: Queen Kane's war council
is mobilizing her armies.

302
00:26:08.255 --> 00:26:11.610
And we've learned from the Payan defector

303
00:26:11.634 --> 00:26:14.363
that not only has
Princess Maghra returned.

304
00:26:14.387 --> 00:26:17.907
but she comes with two grown children.
Haniwa and Kofun.

305
00:26:18.557 --> 00:26:19.826
Both sighted.

306
00:26:19.850 --> 00:26:23.281
The Payan fanatics
will burn them at the stake.

307
00:26:23.896 --> 00:26:25.749
EDO VOSS: They will do
as their queen commands.

308
00:26:25.773 --> 00:26:29.357
With two sighted children
in the royal family now of age.

309
00:26:29.443 --> 00:26:31.171
they are an even greater threat.

310
00:26:31.195 --> 00:26:33.423
THE MILITARY: We don't know
their intentions.

311
00:26:33.447 --> 00:26:34.591
We know they took the trouble

312
00:26:34.615 --> 00:26:37.803
to break their Witchfinder General
out of captivity.

313
00:26:37.827 --> 00:26:40.347
That is intention enough.
We must strike now.

314
00:26:40.371 --> 00:26:44.594
It would be suicide
for the Payans to attack us.

315
00:26:45.501 --> 00:26:48.855
The queen may be crazy.
but she's not a fool.

316
00:26:48.879 --> 00:26:52.185
Still. these are troubling developments.

317
00:26:52.925 --> 00:26:54.277
I can muster our forces in a matter of d...

318
00:26:54.301 --> 00:26:55.938
No. steady. Edo.

319
00:26:56.512 --> 00:27:00.075
The Ganites
are still raining shit on us out west.

320
00:27:00.099 --> 00:27:03.161
And you yourself stood here
and heard the council's attitude

321
00:27:03.185 --> 00:27:04.788
about an eastern campaign.

322
00:27:04.812 --> 00:27:08.208
- You will never sell it.
- No. You will do that.

323
00:27:08.232 --> 00:27:10.502
THE MILITARY: You overestimate
my influence.

324
00:27:10.526 --> 00:27:13.164
I am but one third of the Triangle.

325
00:27:14.697 --> 00:27:16.042
But still.

326
00:27:16.407 --> 00:27:20.929
I will convince the council to request
a diplomatic summit with the Payans.

327
00:27:20.953 --> 00:27:24.921
- Trivantians do not sue for peace!
- We do what we need to do.

328
00:27:25.249 --> 00:27:28.429
And you will do as ordered.
Do you understand?

329
00:27:31.380 --> 00:27:32.566
Yes. sir.

330
00:27:32.590 --> 00:27:36.611
If for nothing else. it will give us time
to bring a battalion or two east.

331
00:27:36.635 --> 00:27:39.357
if it comes to that.

332
00:27:39.680 --> 00:27:41.317
Understood.

333
00:27:44.393 --> 00:27:48.199
I will let you know
what the council decides.

334
00:28:03.287 --> 00:28:07.517
BOW LION: Breathe slow and deep. Baba.
and drink this.

335
00:28:07.541 --> 00:28:11.229
(TAPPING CUP)

336
00:28:11.253 --> 00:28:13.720
- It will give you strength.
- (SIGHS)

337
00:28:19.720 --> 00:28:22.442
(GROANS)
When did you become a healer?

338
00:28:23.391 --> 00:28:27.572
I'm not yet. but I've been learning
from the healers here.

339
00:28:30.022 --> 00:28:34.310
Those roots should absorb the infections
so that the fever can pass.

340
00:28:34.610 --> 00:28:38.666
You've lost so much.
all because of us.

341
00:28:40.366 --> 00:28:42.046
Still. you take us in.

342
00:28:46.163 --> 00:28:48.630
BOW LION: We are one tribe. remember?

343
00:28:52.378 --> 00:28:53.973
Yeah. I remember.

344
00:29:23.701 --> 00:29:27.048
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

345
00:29:38.090 --> 00:29:39.644
(BELLS JINGLING)

346
00:29:40.217 --> 00:29:41.562
MAGHRA: Kofun?

347
00:29:42.178 --> 00:29:44.357
HARLAN: No.
Not Kofun.

348
00:29:46.265 --> 00:29:48.452
MAGHRA: What are you doing in here?

349
00:29:48.476 --> 00:29:52.281
Maghra. it's our wedding night.
Where else am I gonna be?

350
00:29:53.356 --> 00:29:55.334
(BELLS JINGLING)

351
00:29:55.358 --> 00:29:58.371
This is not a marriage.
This is an alliance.

352
00:29:58.527 --> 00:30:02.041
Right. but...
but it can be both.

353
00:30:06.619 --> 00:30:09.486
Put on your pants. Harlan.
I need your help.

354
00:30:10.915 --> 00:30:12.468
- Now.
- Fine.

355
00:30:14.710 --> 00:30:16.055
(HARLAN GRUNTS)

356
00:30:31.143 --> 00:30:33.489
(TAPPING)

357
00:30:36.691 --> 00:30:39.591
They made me sneak you
some pheasant and ale.

358
00:30:39.777 --> 00:30:43.809
Don't worry. I didn't poison it.
if that's what you're thinking.

359
00:30:44.740 --> 00:30:46.420
I had no such thought.

360
00:30:46.784 --> 00:30:48.679
And I had no such poison.

361
00:30:48.703 --> 00:30:49.930
(PLATE CLATTERS)

362
00:30:49.954 --> 00:30:51.758
(LIQUID SLOSHES)

363
00:30:53.082 --> 00:30:55.435
ANDAL: Our Alkenny brothers and sisters.

364
00:30:55.459 --> 00:30:58.556
last time you came to us.
we turned you away.

365
00:30:58.754 --> 00:31:02.526
You healed our Bow Lion.
It is more than we could've hoped for.

366
00:31:02.550 --> 00:31:06.564
It is you who bring us
a message of hope upon your return.

367
00:31:06.679 --> 00:31:09.199
We feared that you would
lead Witchfinders to us.

368
00:31:09.223 --> 00:31:14.121
because when they had come prior. they
said the sighted hid amongst the Alkenny.

369
00:31:14.145 --> 00:31:15.205
- (SWORDS CLASHING)
- (WOMEN SCREAMING)

370
00:31:15.229 --> 00:31:19.494
<i>They slaughtered men.
women. children.</i>

371
00:31:20.401 --> 00:31:22.601
<i>Their blades didn't discriminate.</i>

372
00:31:23.237 --> 00:31:26.591
<i>all because the Witchfinders believed
we had knowledge of witches.</i>

373
00:31:26.615 --> 00:31:27.509
(SCREAMS ECHOING)

374
00:31:27.533 --> 00:31:31.181
<i>Those of us who lived
were spared only to spread the fear.</i>

375
00:31:33.080 --> 00:31:37.428
But we will rebuild.
We're already making babies.

376
00:31:37.918 --> 00:31:42.858
<i>We will make ourselves whole to honor
the memory of the many that were lost.</i>

377
00:31:42.882 --> 00:31:45.819
(SCREAMS ECHOING)

378
00:31:45.843 --> 00:31:47.271
Stop!

379
00:31:49.597 --> 00:31:54.036
ANDAL: <i>And now word comes that the queen
will no longer send her Witchfinders.</i>

380
00:31:54.060 --> 00:31:56.593
<i>as she no longer searches for witches.</i>

381
00:31:58.481 --> 00:32:00.584
The queen may yet change her mind.

382
00:32:00.608 --> 00:32:06.757
but tonight. we celebrate your escape
from Trivantes and savor our freedom…

383
00:32:06.781 --> 00:32:08.467
(SIGNALING)
<i>Tamacti Jun is here.</i>

384
00:32:08.491 --> 00:32:11.803
…however short-lived.
from the queen and her Witchfinders.

385
00:32:11.827 --> 00:32:13.180
(TAPPING)

386
00:32:13.204 --> 00:32:15.599
ANDAL: These are uncertain times.

387
00:32:15.623 --> 00:32:17.684
but we face them with hope

388
00:32:17.708 --> 00:32:21.139
for a future more peaceful than our past.

389
00:32:22.755 --> 00:32:24.559
(GRUNTS)

390
00:32:25.383 --> 00:32:27.783
- Have you lost your mind?
- (GRUNTS)

391
00:32:28.260 --> 00:32:32.032
The Valier deserve retribution.
I owe 'em that much.

392
00:32:32.056 --> 00:32:33.700
BABA VOSS: No.
you owe me. Witchfinder.

393
00:32:33.724 --> 00:32:38.332
You think I don't wanna rip your throat
out every time I hear your voice?

394
00:32:39.230 --> 00:32:41.284
You slaughtered my people too.

395
00:32:42.692 --> 00:32:44.620
But you do not get to die.

396
00:32:45.277 --> 00:32:48.861
Your punishment is you will live
with what you have done.

397
00:32:51.909 --> 00:32:55.764
Death must be earned too. Witchfinder.
every bit as much as life.

398
00:32:55.788 --> 00:32:58.968
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

399
00:33:19.562 --> 00:33:21.491
That's his favorite spot.

400
00:33:22.857 --> 00:33:26.871
And… his favorite chair.

401
00:33:27.820 --> 00:33:29.631
- Kerrigan. Come on.
- (GROANS)

402
00:33:29.655 --> 00:33:31.335
Wake the fuck up.
Come on.

403
00:33:32.825 --> 00:33:36.680
(SNIFFS) Princess.
(SIGHS)

404
00:33:36.704 --> 00:33:39.237
I can still smell the blossoms on you.

405
00:33:39.707 --> 00:33:43.437
You two should be home.
rolling around in sticky sheets.

406
00:33:43.461 --> 00:33:44.688
I need your help.

407
00:33:44.712 --> 00:33:49.560
- Brother. not up to the task?
- We need you to cross the border.

408
00:33:51.802 --> 00:33:53.564
What's the cargo?

409
00:33:53.804 --> 00:33:55.650
Her daughter. Haniwa.

410
00:33:56.807 --> 00:33:59.474
She's being held by the Trivantian army.

411
00:33:59.935 --> 00:34:01.864
- Oh.
- Yeah.

412
00:34:02.229 --> 00:34:03.783
Yeah. fuck off.

413
00:34:04.106 --> 00:34:05.459
Please.

414
00:34:05.483 --> 00:34:09.212
KERRIGAN: Princess. generally in my trade.

415
00:34:09.236 --> 00:34:12.299
the object is to avoid the military.
not go searching for them.

416
00:34:12.323 --> 00:34:13.634
Kerrigan.

417
00:34:13.658 --> 00:34:16.462
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

418
00:34:20.705 --> 00:34:24.770
If she really is in a military brig.
I won't be able to get her out.

419
00:34:24.794 --> 00:34:29.065
Come on. Prison guards can be bought.
same as anybody else.

420
00:34:29.089 --> 00:34:30.442
KERRIGAN: Maybe.

421
00:34:30.466 --> 00:34:33.070
But it would take a lot of copper.

422
00:34:33.094 --> 00:34:34.730
For you or for them?

423
00:34:35.763 --> 00:34:38.817
- I am offended. Princess.
- No. he's not.

424
00:34:40.017 --> 00:34:44.324
No. I suppose I'm not.
Still. it would take some doing.

425
00:34:44.480 --> 00:34:48.512
When you find her. how will you
get her safely out of Trivantes?

426
00:34:48.901 --> 00:34:50.963
KERRIGAN: Ah. getting out of the city's
the easy part.

427
00:34:50.987 --> 00:34:56.044
I have been smuggling Ganite thornflower
from Trivantes to Pennsa for years.

428
00:34:58.411 --> 00:35:04.685
I know every hole and tunnel
into and out of that place.

429
00:35:04.709 --> 00:35:07.555
- (INHALES. GROANS)
- So you'll do it?

430
00:35:10.464 --> 00:35:16.522
(INHALES)
Uh. consider it. um. a wedding gift.

431
00:35:17.805 --> 00:35:19.157
(YAWNS)

432
00:35:19.181 --> 00:35:21.868
I'll leave when the God Flame warms.

433
00:35:21.892 --> 00:35:24.287
- (KERRIGAN YAWNS)
- You'll leave now.

434
00:35:24.311 --> 00:35:27.158
(KISSES) Come on.
Up you get.

435
00:36:03.893 --> 00:36:06.531
PARIS: No.
Now is not the time.

436
00:36:08.814 --> 00:36:11.376
Paris? How could you bring him here?

437
00:36:11.400 --> 00:36:13.920
How could you even
share the air that he breathes?

438
00:36:13.944 --> 00:36:16.673
We need him.
He has a new purpose.

439
00:36:16.697 --> 00:36:20.253
No. He dies by my hand tonight.

440
00:36:21.285 --> 00:36:23.430
(BREATHES SHAKILY)
He killed my mother.

441
00:36:23.454 --> 00:36:26.968
Yes. Time will come he pays for that.

442
00:36:27.500 --> 00:36:29.470
I can't believe this is you.

443
00:36:30.878 --> 00:36:32.306
You're a traitor.

444
00:36:32.505 --> 00:36:35.150
He is our only hope of getting to Maghra.

445
00:36:35.174 --> 00:36:37.937
The Witchfinders massacred the Valier.

446
00:36:39.220 --> 00:36:40.947
They will have
something to say about this.

447
00:36:40.971 --> 00:36:45.194
Please. You cannot tell them.
You cannot.

448
00:36:47.019 --> 00:36:50.491
- I trusted you. I trusted you.
- Bow Lion. Bow Lion.

449
00:36:51.732 --> 00:36:53.077
You know me.

450
00:36:54.235 --> 00:36:56.831
You know my heart.

451
00:36:59.198 --> 00:37:01.002
- Girl.
- (CRIES)

452
00:37:03.285 --> 00:37:06.485
(BOW LION SNIFFLES)
Be gone before God Flame rises.

453
00:37:08.708 --> 00:37:11.608
I won't keep your secret
any longer than that.

454
00:37:37.987 --> 00:37:39.332
Kofun?

455
00:37:40.406 --> 00:37:42.543
(SNAPPING)

456
00:37:44.910 --> 00:37:47.973
(SIGHS)
Thank God Flame.

457
00:37:47.997 --> 00:37:49.676
(SIGHS)

458
00:37:49.874 --> 00:37:52.637
- I told you to stay in my room.
- I know.

459
00:37:53.252 --> 00:37:58.142
- I'm here.
- (MAGHRA BREATHES DEEPLY)

460
00:37:58.382 --> 00:37:59.894
I'm sorry.

461
00:38:01.635 --> 00:38:06.033
I know this must all feel very strange
and upsetting to you.

462
00:38:06.057 --> 00:38:08.945
and I promise you
I will explain everything.

463
00:38:09.185 --> 00:38:12.039
but you cannot disobey me like that again.

464
00:38:12.063 --> 00:38:13.783
It is not safe here.

465
00:38:14.565 --> 00:38:17.098
- My sister is someone who...
- Sibeth.

466
00:38:18.486 --> 00:38:20.540
Don't worry.
We've met.

467
00:38:21.822 --> 00:38:24.289
She came to see me
after your wedding.

468
00:38:27.787 --> 00:38:29.173
Kofun.

469
00:38:31.707 --> 00:38:34.374
- You cannot trust her.
- KOFUN: Why not?

470
00:38:35.086 --> 00:38:38.094
She's not the one
who lied to me my entire life.

471
00:38:38.506 --> 00:38:39.851
(SIGHS)

472
00:38:40.591 --> 00:38:42.152
It is not that simple.

473
00:38:42.176 --> 00:38:43.570
(SNAPS)

474
00:38:43.594 --> 00:38:45.861
You betrayed your husband tonight.

475
00:38:46.639 --> 00:38:49.944
You betrayed all of us
and not for the first time.

476
00:38:51.018 --> 00:38:55.374
You could've identified yourself
to the Witchfinders when we were babies.

477
00:38:55.398 --> 00:38:57.668
You could've saved the Alkenny.

478
00:38:57.692 --> 00:38:59.461
We wouldn't have had to
spend our entire lives running.

479
00:38:59.485 --> 00:39:04.413
My sister would never have accepted
any sighted children that weren't her own.

480
00:39:05.241 --> 00:39:07.594
She would've killed all of us.

481
00:39:07.618 --> 00:39:10.180
I was trying to protect you
the best way I knew how.

482
00:39:10.204 --> 00:39:12.432
- By lying to us.
- Of course by lying to you.

483
00:39:12.456 --> 00:39:14.226
The truth would've gotten you
burned at the stake.

484
00:39:14.250 --> 00:39:15.595
No.

485
00:39:16.252 --> 00:39:21.934
You resented us.
You resented our sight. You always have.

486
00:39:22.591 --> 00:39:26.879
That's why you were so angry
when you realized we'd learned to read.

487
00:39:26.971 --> 00:39:28.316
Wasn't it?

488
00:39:29.640 --> 00:39:34.113
You wouldn't speak to us.
We'd become unrecognizable you said.

489
00:39:34.520 --> 00:39:37.325
Do you recognize yourself. Mama?

490
00:39:39.275 --> 00:39:40.787
Because I don't.

491
00:39:41.861 --> 00:39:46.668
You and Haniwa belong to a world
that I couldn't begin to understand.

492
00:39:48.034 --> 00:39:51.810
I was terrified that one day
it would take you away from me.

493
00:39:55.750 --> 00:39:57.387
Looks like it did.

494
00:40:02.840 --> 00:40:05.507
What are you doing about Haniwa and Dad?

495
00:40:07.762 --> 00:40:10.898
Lord Harlan has already
sent someone to find them.

496
00:40:12.224 --> 00:40:13.569
(SCOFFS)

497
00:40:14.977 --> 00:40:16.913
(LAUGHS)

498
00:40:16.937 --> 00:40:21.545
Right. I'm sure your new husband
is very determined to find your old one.

499
00:40:44.048 --> 00:40:49.022
(TAMACTI JUN SNIFFS. EXHALES)

500
00:40:54.016 --> 00:40:58.698
You asked me
if I remember how many I had killed.

501
00:41:02.108 --> 00:41:05.872
That's like me asking you
how many breaths you took today.

502
00:41:21.252 --> 00:41:25.558
When the queen left me bleeding to death…

503
00:41:27.883 --> 00:41:30.021
I fell into a state.

504
00:41:31.679 --> 00:41:36.110
Not dead…
but no longer among the living.

505
00:41:40.062 --> 00:41:41.866
And it was there…

506
00:41:43.399 --> 00:41:44.952
Suddenly…

507
00:41:47.403 --> 00:41:49.082
I had vision.

508
00:41:52.074 --> 00:41:54.629
(SNIFFS)
Do you know what I saw?

509
00:42:01.000 --> 00:42:02.762
I saw faces.

510
00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:08.559
I saw the faces…

511
00:42:08.841 --> 00:42:14.899
Of every man. woman and child
that I had murdered and tortured.

512
00:42:18.559 --> 00:42:20.446
I heard their screams.

513
00:42:22.813 --> 00:42:24.909
I could feel their pain.

514
00:42:30.112 --> 00:42:33.167
But in all of those faces…

515
00:42:35.451 --> 00:42:41.467
I could not find that of my wife
nor of my children.

516
00:42:46.045 --> 00:42:52.603
I was not there when Queen Kane
drowned them in their beds.

517
00:42:59.433 --> 00:43:01.029
Instead…

518
00:43:03.604 --> 00:43:08.536
I was butchering all those faces.

519
00:43:10.987 --> 00:43:16.210
For years and years.
you have fought for darkness.

520
00:43:19.161 --> 00:43:22.342
Now you must fight for light.

521
00:43:26.585 --> 00:43:29.349
You should not have stopped the girl.

522
00:43:35.011 --> 00:43:36.356
(GRUNTS)

523
00:43:36.595 --> 00:43:41.027
All right. No more stopping.
We walk until we reach Pennsa.

524
00:43:41.642 --> 00:43:42.987
Do not fear.

525
00:43:44.478 --> 00:43:48.333
You will have
plenty of opportunities to die.

526
00:43:48.357 --> 00:43:49.744
(SNIFFS)

527
00:43:50.067 --> 00:43:51.621
We all will.

528
00:43:53.779 --> 00:43:58.544
HANIWA: I always thought that
the fact that I could see and you couldn't

529
00:43:58.993 --> 00:44:01.172
was something that separated us.

530
00:44:02.496 --> 00:44:05.296
Thought there was
so much space between us.

531
00:44:05.333 --> 00:44:09.764
But every time
I feel like I'm beyond help.

532
00:44:10.629 --> 00:44:16.187
in the House of Enlightenment.
in Trivantes. somehow you always find me.

533
00:44:19.305 --> 00:44:24.362
You're my baby girl.
Kofun is my boy. Maghra my wife.

534
00:44:24.894 --> 00:44:29.784
As long as I'm alive.
nothing will separate us. Yes.

535
00:44:33.569 --> 00:44:35.498
I know I don't make it easy.

536
00:44:38.074 --> 00:44:39.627
No. you don't.

537
00:44:40.993 --> 00:44:43.660
From this place.
it's two days to Pennsa.

538
00:44:45.539 --> 00:44:48.386
What do you think it will be like. Pennsa?

539
00:44:49.877 --> 00:44:51.222
Crowded.

540
00:44:52.213 --> 00:44:55.184
(CHUCKLES)
What do you think she'll be like?

541
00:44:56.217 --> 00:44:58.980
- Uh. she'll be like Maghra.
- Right.

542
00:45:00.554 --> 00:45:02.817
Do we even know who that is?

542
00:45:03.305 --> 00:46:03.315
